-- Bayer Seeks Buyers for Diabetes Device Business, FTD Reports
-- B y   A l e x   W e b b
-- 2012-05-08T18:50:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-08/bayer-seeks-buyers-for-diabetes-device-business-ftd-reports.html
Bayer AG (BAYN)  plans to sell its diabetes
measurement devices business, the  Financial Times Deutschland 
reported in a preview of an article to be published tomorrow,
citing unidentified people with knowledge of the prospective
sale.  Bayer has already held talks with competitors about a deal
for the unit, which has annual revenue of around 1 billion euros
($1.3 billion), the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Webb  in Frankfurt at 
 awebb25@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chad Thomas at   cthomas16@bloomberg.net . 